alarm-inventory-list.description: The SWDL_CHGMNG_NOMATCH is an alarm indicating that the NE software package and any one board software do not match.
The KMC key fails to synchronize with APPs.
Batch backup failure of the SCC board data.
Alarm storm. Certain alarms on the SCC board may be lost when the alarm queue is full. This alarm indicates that the alarm module is in the alarm storm state.
The space of the flash file system is insufficient.

The BOOTROM_BAD is an alarm indicating the BOOTROM data check failure. During the running of board software, the system periodically checks whether the BOOTROM data is damaged. This alarm occurs when the BOOTROM data is detected damaged.
DIFFERENT SUBNET ARE MIXED-UP
Loopback alarm.
The configured DCN subnet ID has not been committed.
This alarm is generated when the total service packet traffic exceeds the hardware forwarding capability.
Patch package matching failure.
Loss of NE software.
Indicates that a node on the EPRS ring is faulty.
This alarm is reported when configuration persistency occurs in the database in some scenarios.
If the local port is in the auto-negotiation mode and the remote port is not, the local port reports the working mode mismatch alarm.
The ALM_APS_MANU_STOP is an alarm indicating that the MSP protocol is manually stopped.
Thg FAN_AGING is an alarm indicating that the fan speed is less that 80% of its rated speed.
No license file.
The ETH_LOS is an alarm indicating loss of network port connection. This alarm occurs when the Ethernet network port cannot receive Ethernet signals.
Status of an SDH MSP group.
This alarm indicates that the NE is in the unsync state.The alarm is cleared when the NTP turns into the sync state.
Exclusion of a patch package board.
The ENERGY_SAVING_CFG_MISMATCH alarm indicates that the NE energy saving configurations at both ends of a link are inconsistent.
The DBMS_PROTECT_MODE is an alarm indicating that the NE database enters the protection mode.
The NE database is deleted.
A member in a PLA group is unavailable.
Certificate file of SSL is not encrypted.
Board not in position alarm.
The IN_PWR_ABN is an alarm indicating that the input optical power is asbnormal.
The SLAVE_BAD is an alarm indicating that the alarmed board detects a fault of the connector between itself and the standby SCC board.
The LASER_SHUT is an alarm indicating that the laser of the board is shut down.

The K1_K2_M is an alarm indicating the mismatch between the K1 and K2 bytes. This alarm occurs, when the path numbers indicated in the transmitted K1 byte and the received K2 byte are inconsistent and the inconsistency lasts for a time period (160 ms by default).
The SWDL_NEPKGCHECK is an alarm indicating that a file in the software package is lost or the package loading fails to pass the check.

The PATCH_OP_TIMEOUT is an alarm indicating that the duration for the patch package to be in the downloading or activation completion state exceeds the upper limit and the patch package needs to be manually processed.
The RTC_FAIL is an alarm of SCC real time clock (RTC) failure. This alarm occurs when the clock of the SCC is faulty.
A PLA group is unavailable.

The ETH_NO_FLOW is an alarm indicating no more received or transmitted traffic for some performance object, such as port, flow, queue etc. This alarm is reported when the objects are enabled but has no flow.
An error occurs when a PLA group generates packets.
The FLOW_OVER is an alarm indicating the inflow at the Ethernet port crosses the threshold. When the received traffic at the Ethernet port exceeds the expected traffic, this alarm occurs.

When network route to NMS port conflict with other direct DCN OSPF network route, and the latters mask is longer than the formers, it may cause PC communication problem. When there are more than one conflict routes, report the one has the longest mask.
Ne Id conflict.
State of auto-synchronization disabled.
Files in the USB flash drive are not encrypted, an exception occurs during the integrity check, or decryption fails.
The SWDL_PKG_NOBDSOFT is an alarm indicating that the files of some boards are not in the software package for loading.
Bit error threshold-crossing detected at MAC layer.
The SWDL_COMMIT_FAIL is an alarm indicating that the commit operation fails for some boards.
Bd software uncommited need to commit it
The number of TCP connections between NEs running the automatically extended ECC protocol exceeds the system limit.
The SYSLOG_COMM_FAIL is an alarm that occurs when the NE and the SYSLOG server have an abnormal connection or session in the TCP mode.
APS status indication.
The BIOS_STATUS is an alarm indicating that the board cannot reach a normal software running status.
The SWDL_BD_MATCH_FAIL is an alarm indicating that a board fails to match the board software.
The SWDL_ACTIVATED_TIMEOUT is an alarm indicating that during software package loading, the NE does not perform the commit operation in a certain time after the board is activated.
The SWDL_AUTOMATCH_INH is an alarm indicating that the automatic match function is disabled.
The PLA_CFG_MISMATCH alarm indicates that the NE PLA configurations at both ends of a link are inconsistent.
The LSR_NO_FITED is an alarm indicating that the laser is not installed. This alarm occurs when the optical interface is enabled but not installed with the optical module.
Ethernet OAM(802.3ah)self loop alarm.
Ethernet communication failure. The alarm occurs when the external Ethernet communication and the network port fail.
The number of DCN OSPF neighbors excesses the suggested threshold.

Software difference between working and protection boards alarm. The two file systems of the SCC board are backup for each other. Each file is saved in the two file systems. The alarm occurs when the software versions in the two file systems are not consistent or the versions of the files with the same name are not consistent.
The mac of static arp set by user is unequal to the actual mac address.
After the system control board is replaced, the board patch version is inconsistent with the patch package version.
An alarm is reported if any default password of the default user is not changed in time.
License expired.
The temperature threshold crossing alarm.
This alarm is generated when a user-defined SSL certificate file is damaged.
Remote link event.
This alarm is reported when the system control board does not launch a board patch match for specific reasons.
The number of NEs in a DCN subnet exceeds the setting threshold.
This alarm is generated if an NE IP address conflict occurs.
The SSL certificate file is to expire or expired.
There is an error in the storage.
APS protection switching failure.
License in keepalive period
When the LPT triggers the shutdown of the physical port, the alarm that indicates automatic link down should be reported.
The capacity exceeds the limitation specified by the license.

The LPS_UNI_BI_M is an alarm indicating the mismatch of the single-ended and dual-ended modes in a linear MSP. This alarm is applicable to a linear MSP only. This alarm occurs, when the opposite end single-ended/dual-ended mode indicated by the lower three bits of the K2 byte is inconsistent with the local end single-ended/dual-ended mode, and when the inconsistency lasts for a time period (2s by default).
This alarm is generated if the user password encryption mode is MD5 or SHA256 when a user logs in, changes the password, or adds another user.
Discovery failure.
This alarm is generated when the device authentication function is enabled but fails.
The more limited set threshold, the software MAC chip timing detection and error the number of bytes received bytes, calculates the error is more than the threshold.
This alarm occurs when service loopback is set.

The WRG_BD_TYPE is an alarm of wrong board type. This alarm occurs when the types of the logical board and the physical board are different.This alarm occurs when the types of the logical board is not supported by the current device.
The BUS_ERR is a bus error alarm. This alarm occurs when the bus is abnormal.
The current NE is within the license trial period that lasts for 90 days.
This alarm is generated when the patch initialization fails.
Remote failure.
The DCN_CHANNEL_BITERROR alarm indicates bit errors on the DCN channel, which may cause DCN communication interruption.
There is an error in the system database.
The LSR_WILL_DIE is an alarm indicating that the laser is going to stop working. This alarm occurs when the laser is unavailable.
The SECU_ALM is an alarm indicating that an illegal user fails to log in to the NE.
The SEC_RADIUS_FAIL is an alarm indicating that a large number of authentification failures occur on the NE within a short period.
This alarm occurs when the fan is faulty.
The TF is an alarm of laser transmission failure. This alarm occurs when a board detects that the output optical power of the laser exceeds the set failure alarm threshold.
The SWDL_INPROCESS is an alarm indicating that the NE is loading the software package.
The number of gateway connections exceeds the threshold.
The PORT_EXC_TRAFFIC is an alarm indicating the traffic utilization at the Ethernet port over the threshold. When the received or transmitted traffic exceeds the expected traffic, this alarm occurs.
The POWER_ALM is an alarm indicating that the voltage of the board power module is beyond the normal range.
The OUT_PWR_ABN is an alarm indicating that the output optical power is abnormal.
The CA_CFG_MISMATCH alarm indicates that the CA configurations are inconsistent.
Data recovery from or data backup to a USB disk fails.
Patch package file error.
The LASER_MOD_ERR is an alarm indicating mismatch of optical modules. When the type of the optical module inserted does not match the type supported by the board, this alarm occurs.
The SWDL_PKGVER_MM is an alarm indicating that the consistency check of the software package version fails.

The TR_LOC is an alarm indicating that the clock of the cross-connect board is faulty. If a board has detected loss of the clock signal of the cross-connect board, loss of the frame header, or damage to the cross-connect board, the TR_LOC alarm is reported.
The SWDL_ROLLBACK_FAIL is an alarm indicating that some board rollback fails when the NE performs rollback.

The K2_M is an alarm of K2 byte mismatch. This alarm occurs, when the opposite end protection mode indicated by the fifth bit (counted from the highest bit to the lowest bit) of the K2 byte is inconsistent with the local end protection mode, and when the inconsistency lasts for a time period (2s by default).
This alarm is reported when the rates of protocol packets received by a device exceed the upper rate threshold for 30 consecutive seconds.
One cascading port is configured in a working group (for example, a CA group), but the other cascading port that is actually connected is not in the working group.

The BD_NOT_INSTALLED is an alarm indicating that the logical board is not installed in the corresponding slot. This alarm occurs when a physical board is installed but no logical board is created on the T2000.
This alarm occurs when the board detects a hardware exception.
The space of the memory file system is insufficient.
